This paper deals with the assessment of risk in the fairness domain, which is a topic that falls under the category of Cybersecurity and Privacy (cs.CY). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms and human input, which are relevant to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the construction of hybrid models, which could be relevant to the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the prediction of recidivism, which is a topic that falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
